<item>
            <title>[FELIX-6168] Enable WebConsole login only after specified Security Providers are present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-6168</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to configure the WebConsole to only accept logins after specified Security Providers are found. &lt;br/&gt;
If these security providers are not yet registered in the Service Registry, logging in should be disabled. The local plain username/password approach should not provide the opportunity to log in, in that case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The configuration to enable this should be provided as a framework property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This approach is similar to what has been implemented for ConfigAdmin in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-6059&quot; title=&quot;Improve usability for ConfigurationPlugins&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-6059&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-6059&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
