                            <comment id="16906071" author="cziegeler" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2019 10:48:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bosschaert&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bosschaert&quot;&gt;bosschaert&lt;/a&gt; I think it would also make sense to require a specific authentication plugin (by referencing some service property like a name, id etc.). This way it can be ensured that the web console is only active if such an auth plugin is available&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
